 East London - Cambridge police busted a man for the illegal possession of a huge amount of abalone, lobsters and crab. "A crime intelligence driven operation resulted in the arrest of a 34-year-old man in a house at Vincent, East London," said police spokesperson, Captain Mluleki Mbi. "Over 120kg of abalone, redlobsters, crabs and dotted fish were found stashed in freezers. "The estimated street value is over R100 000." Capt Mbi said that the man will appear before the East London Magistrate's court on soon facing charges of contravening the Living Marine Resources Act. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  